======
Magnet 
======
April 2, 2009

Interacting message agents.



Pole - Application messages
---------------------------
Poles are Twisted services that know how to handle messages passed carried
within the Transport Protocols content payload. 

Poles realize the intent/purpose/request carried within the Application
message.

A Pole is a collection of methods/functions that execute specific actions.
Actions can be anything. 


Field - Transport messages
--------------------------
Magnet supports AMQP version 0-8.

The AMQP specification defines several exchange types and a range of
message queue configuration options. 


Particle - Message format and serialization
-------------------------------------------


Usage
=====
Magnet can be used as a twistd plugin:

$ twistd magnet --help
Usage: twistd [options] magnet [options]
Options:
  -h, --host=       Broker Host [default: localhost]
      --port=       Broker Port [default: 5672]
  -u, --username=   Broker username [default: guest]
  -p, --password=   Broker password [default: guest]
      --vhost=      Broker vhost [default: /]
      --spec_path=  Path to AMQP spec file [default:]
      --version     
      --help        Display this help and exit.
      --plugins     

Create a simple actor (look for this in the examples dir).
cd into the examples dir (you should see a dir called twisted).
Run the say actor by doing:
twistd -n magnet 

Magnet will automatically find say with in twisted/plugins/say_agent.py

Simple Producer
---------------

twistd -n magnet send -c say -r test --payload='ohi, wrld'


Notes:
------
Message factories. 
Given a message protocol/format/..., create instances of message handlers
or create a parameterized message object ready for placement into the
transport message body/content.


INSTALLATION
============

Dependencies
------------
Python - http://python.org  (Comes with in OSX and Linux)
Twisted - http://twistedmatrix.com/trac/ (Comes with OSX)
txAMQP - https://launchpad.net/txamqp/+download

AMQP Broker
-----------
RabbitMQ is the only tested and supported broker (spec version amqp0-8).

http://www.rabbitmq.com/download.html



